definitions.explanation_en: A surname of Scottish origin, historically associated with the Clan Cunningham in Ayrshire, Scotland. It is used as a family name and does not carry a general semantic meaning outside of personal identification.
definitions.explanation_cn: 源自苏格兰的姓氏，历史上与阿耶尔郡的库宁汉氏族相关，仅作为家族名称使用，不具有个人身份之外的普遍语义。
definitions.example_en: Dr. Cunningham presented her research on quantum computing at the international conference.
definitions.example_cn: 库宁汉博士在国际会议上展示了她关于量子计算的研究。
